p, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Pulford","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Pulford in Cheshire, so called from Old English <i>pōl</i> ‘pool, pond’ or perhaps <i>pull</i> ‘pool, creek’ + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Robert de Pulford III was born before 1159, in Pulford, Cheshire, England. He had at least 1 son with Jane de Polford. He died before 1159, in his hometown."},"et":{"bef 1159–abt 1244":"enne 1159–enne 1159","1180–1228":"1180–1228","1190–1243":"1190–1243","1159–1159":"1159–1159","1190":"1190","1228":"1228","bef 1159":"enne 1159","1159":"1159","1243":"1243","abt 1244":"enne 1159","1180":"1180","Pulford, Cheshire, England":"Pulford, Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"bef 1159–abt 1244":"ennen vuotta 1159–ennen vuotta 1159","1180–1228":"1180–1228","1190–1243":"1190–1243","1159–1159":"1159–1159","1190":"1190","1228":"1228","bef 1159":"ennen vuotta 1159","1159":"1159","1243":"1243","abt 1244":"ennen vuotta 1159","1180":"1180","Pulford, Cheshire, England":"Pulford, Cheshire, England"},"fr":{"bef 1159–abt 1244":"avant 1159–avant 1159","1180–1228":"1180–1228","1190–1243":"1190–1243","1159–1159":"1159–1159","1190":"1190","1228":"1228","bef 1159":"avant 1159","1159":"1159","1243":"1243","abt 1244":"avant 1159","1180":"1180","Pulford, Cheshire, England":"Pulford, Cheshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Sir Robert de Pulford III est né avant 1159, à Pulford, Cheshire, Angleterre. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Jane de Polford. Il est décédé avant 1159, dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"bef 1159–abt 1244":"vor 1159–vor 1159","1180–1228":"1180–1228","1190–1243":"1190–1243","1159–1159":"1159–1159","1190":"1190","1228":"1228","bef 1159":"vor 1159","1159":"1159","1243":"1243","abt 1244":"vor 1159","1180":"1180","Pulford, Cheshire, England":"Pulford, Cheshire, England","lifeSummary":"Sir Robert de Pulford III wurde vor 1159 in Pulford, Cheshire, England geboren. Er hatte mit Jane de Polford mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb vor 1159 in seinem Geburtsort."},"ht":{"bef 1159–abt 1244":"before 1159–before 1159","1180–1228":"1180–1228","1190–1243":"1190–1243","1159–1159":"1159–1159","1190":"1190","1228":"1228","bef 1159":"before 1159","1159":"1159","1243":"1243","abt 1244":"before 1159","1180":"1180","Pulford, Cheshire, England":"Pulford, Cheshire, England"},"hu":{"bef 1159–abt 1244":"1159 előtt–1159 előtt","1180–1228":"1180–1228","1190–1243":"1190–1